  {
    "page": 8,
    "block_id": "page_008:block_046",
    "block_type": "text",
    "text": "Results. Table 8 shows the results. Simple-SZZ-Agent is effec- tive across all tested configurations. Even the cheapest configu- ration (OpenHands with minimax-m2.5 at $0.04 per fix commit) achieves 0.79 F1-score, outperforming all previous non-agentic ap- proaches. The best configuration (OpenHands with Claude Sonnet 4.5) achieves 0.86 F1-score at $0.38 per fix commit, surpassing the Claude Opus 4.5 configurations. Within the same agent framework, more capable models generally perform better, though the differ- ence between Sonnet and Opus is small or even reversed.",
    "bbox": [
